==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trailing
<hw>Trail"ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & vb. n.</pos> from
<er>Trail</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Trailing arbutus</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
under <er>Arbutus</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Trailing spring</b></col>, <cd>a
spring fixed in the axle box of the trailing wheels of a locomotive
engine, and so placed as to assist in deadening any shock which may
occur.</cd> <au>Weale.</au> -- <col><b>Trailing wheel</b></col>, <cd>a
hind wheel of a locomotive when it is not a driving wheel; also, one of
the hind wheels of a carriage.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trailing edge</ent>⟦br⟧
